Class GeneralJimpleProgramState

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.rwth.i2.attestor.programState.GeneralProgramState
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    JimpleProgramState, LabelledProgramState, ProgramState, State, Cloneable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    DefaultProgramState, IndexedState

    public abstract class GeneralJimpleProgramState
extends Object
implements JimpleProgramState
    A general implementation of program states that comprises most functionality when analyzing Jimple programs.

    Christoph

      • leaveScope

        public void leaveScope()
        Description copied from interface: JimpleProgramState
        Manages the scope in order to distinguish variables of the same name, for example within recursion. This method must be called before any value in the calling method is assigned (for example in x = foo(), decrease must be called after evaluating foo() but before the return value is attached to x ).
        Specified by:
        leaveScope in interface JimpleProgramState
